Title : Yoo Jaehoon
Text : {{Multiple issues|{{BLP sources|date=April 2014}}}}

'''Yoo Jaehoon''' is the Director-General and the Controller of the [[Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank]] [[AIIB|(AIIB]]).<ref>[http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3023853/ Korea’s vice president post forfeited at the AIIB]</ref>

== Early life ==
{{unreferenced section|date=July 2019}}
Yoo has a BA in economics and an MA in public administration from [[Seoul National University]], and an MA (DEA) in international economics at [[Sciences Po]]. He graduated from the [[Ecole Nationale d'Administration]] (ENA) in France. He obtained a PhD in economics from [[Kyonggi University]] in 2011.

== Career ==
During his 30-year career in public service, he worked on a variety of projects related to capital market development, financial policy, and international aid for developing countries. 

From 1997 to 2000, Yoo worked as an economist at the [[Asian Development Bank]] in [[Manila]]. HE served as a senior securities market specialist at the [[World Bank]] and [[International Finance Corporation]] between 2005 and 2008. Yoo was the president of the [[Sciences Po|Sciences Po de Paris]] Korean Alumni Association.{{cn|date=July 2019}}

He worked as [[Spokesperson]] for the [[Financial Services Commission (South Korea)|Financial Services Commission]]<ref>[http://www.businessweek.com/stories/2008-09-03/lehman-skeptics-doubt-a-korean-rescuebusinessweek-business-news-stock-market-and-financial-advice Lehman: Skeptics Doubt a Korean Rescue]</ref> from 2008 to 2009. He worked as s Director General of the Treasury Bureau at the [[Ministry of Economy and Finance (South Korea)|Ministry of Strategy and Finance]] <ref>[http://sharenetcfds.co.za/news_disp.php?id=65850 South Korea to buy back T-bonds in March]</ref> from December 2009 to March 2011,. He served as Commissioner of the [[Securities and Futures Commission]]<ref>[http://financialservicescommission.wordpress.com/2013/08/20/sfc-standing-commissioners-meeting-with-foreign-correspondents/ SFC Standing Commissioner’s meeting with foreign correspondents]</ref><ref>[http://societas.aks.ac.kr/english/download.php?id=172&sid=f904d20c124ca3b764539cd7a16ecdbe/ INVITATION TO THE 42ND SOCIETAS KOREANA LECTURE MEETING]</ref> from April 2012. He served as Chairman and CEO of [[Korea Securities Depository]] from November 2013 to October 2016. 

Yoo is Director General and Controller of [[AIIB]]. 

==Publications==
Yoo's publications include ''The Korean Bond Market: The Next Frontiers'' (2008) and ''Development Strategy for China Capital Market'' (2008). He published the papers "Financing Innovation: How to Build an Efficient Exchange for Small Firms" (2008), "Study on the Financial Characteristics and Financing Patterns of Innovative Firms" (2011) and "Creating an Artificial Sun" (2016).

